HEADWORD: demonetization
<hw>de*mon`e*ti*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
demonetizing, or the condition of being demonetized;</def>
<specif>specificially,</specif> <def>the declaration by a government
that something (e.g. gold or silver) is no longer the legal tender of a
country; <as>as, the <ex>demonetization</ex> of gold</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

